3. quaedam loca, 810. This state- ment is very obscure. and would appear as if Tacitus was describing something which he imperfectly understood. Itis not clear whether the colouring was on the exterior or interior surfaces, but it is most probable that the ‘quaedam loca' were certain portious or chambers in· side, and that these were plastered over with coloured earth or earths of such purity and brightness as to correspond in some sort to the Roman wall decorations such as are seen at Pompeii).
